'''''Westward 1847''''' (also punctuated as '''''Westward-1847''''') is a 1979 video game written by Jon C. Sherman published by [[The Software Exchange]] for the [[TRS-80]] 16K. It originally appeared as the cover feature for the October 1979 issue of ''[[SoftSide]]''.<ref name="sherman">{{cite journal |last1=Sherman |first1=Jon C. |title=Westward 1847 |journal=[[SoftSide]] |date=October 1979 |issue=13 |page=37 |url=https://archive.org/details/softside-magazine-13/page/n36}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Westward 1847'' is a game in which the player has 40 weeks to get to Oregon before winter comes.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
Jon Mishcon reviewed ''Westward 1847'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 34.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Mishcon |first=Jon |date=December 1980 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=34|pages=36}}</ref> Mishcon commented that "I recommend this game."<ref name="SG"/>

